Combine apples, rhubarb, 1/2 cup Equal(r) Spoonful* and cornstarch. Place in 1-1/2 quart casserole dish. Combine water, lemon juice and lemon peel. Pour over fruit mixture. Cover and bake in preheated 400 degree F oven 20 to 25 minutes or until fruit is tender. Meanwhile, combine oats, raisins, nuts, 1/3 cup Equal(r) Spoonful**, butter and cinnamon until well blended. Remove cover from fruit mixture. Sprinkle with oats mixture. Return to oven and bake, uncovered, an additional 8 to 10 minutes or until topping is crisp. Serve warm with frozen yogurt, ice cream or whipped topping, if desired.